  "oracle_namespace_origin": {
    "notes": "The fixture-locking parity tests inherit two distinct oracle namespaces. The 9 high-trust oracles O-022..O-030 (level-start-state-hash, bundled-demo-sync, scripted-mechanics, framebuffer-crc, menu-timing, audio-suite, save-load-roundtrip, quirk-regressions, full-shareware-e1-acceptance) come from prior plan_engine and are recorded in plan_engine/REFERENCE_ORACLES.md and the inherited reference/manifests/c1-complete.json acceptance manifest. The 31 oracles OR-FPS-006..OR-FPS-036 come from prior plan_fps and are recorded in plan_fps/REFERENCE_ORACLES.md alongside the plan_fps/manifests/01-015-audit-missing-side-by-side-replay.json side-by-side replay manifest. Both namespaces are read-only prior art under plan_vanilla_parity governance: future fixture-author steps under plan_vanilla_parity Phase 02 (02-005..02-033 oracle captures, 02-034 replace-pending-oracle-fixtures-with-live-evidence, 02-035 gate-oracle-foundation-without-deferred-status) must replace pending fixture contents in place rather than renumber the OR-FPS-* or O-* identifiers, because doing so would break the locking assertions in this 41-test suite.",
