  "boundary_status": {
    "parity_relative_path": "test/parity/",
    "oracle_relative_path": "test/oracles/",
    "fixtures_relative_paths_sorted": ["test/oracles/fixtures/", "test/parity/fixtures/"],
    "manifests_relative_paths_sorted": ["reference/manifests/"],
    "writable_workspace": true,
    "source_only_metadata": true,
    "no_proprietary_bytes_embedded": true,
    "notes": "test/parity/ and test/oracles/ are writable test workspaces that the inventory lane catalogs in this step. Each of the 41 fixture-locking tests reads only repository-committed JSON artifacts (test/parity/fixtures/*.json, test/oracles/fixtures/*.json, reference/manifests/c1-complete.json) and asserts canonical structural and SHA-256 fingerprint expectations against them; tests that additionally cross-check the bundled local DOS executables (test/parity/audio-suite.test.ts, test/parity/final-gate.test.ts, test/parity/framebuffer-crc.test.ts, test/parity/full-e1-acceptance.test.ts, test/oracles/capture-* implementations) do so by reading paths under reference/policy.ts REFERENCE_BUNDLE_PATH at run time without embedding proprietary bytes in the test source or in this inventory. The inventory captures only filename, relative path, size, line count, SHA-256 fingerprint of the test file itself, plus the relative paths and oracle identifiers each test pins. Fixture and manifest contents are not duplicated here; fixture-content metadata (per-fixture sha256 of fixture bytes) is owned by the prior step 01-015 inventory-oracle-fixtures-with-pending-status for test/oracles/fixtures/ and remains unowned for test/parity/fixtures/ until a future Phase 02 oracle step takes responsibility."
  },
  "implications": [
    "The 41 parity tests in this inventory form the executable contract that locks the 9 test/parity/fixtures/ JSON fixtures, the 31 test/oracles/fixtures/ JSON fixtures, and the reference/manifests/c1-complete.json acceptance manifest in place. Any change to these fixture or manifest contents without updating the corresponding test will fail the focused test for that change; conversely any change to the assertion structure of these tests must update the per-test SHA-256 fingerprint recorded in this inventory. The owning step for replacing pending fixture contents with live evidence is plan_vanilla_parity/steps/02-034-replace-pending-oracle-fixtures-with-live-evidence.md, and the gate that closes Phase 02 without deferred-status fixtures remaining is plan_vanilla_parity/steps/02-035-gate-oracle-foundation-without-deferred-status.md.",
    "Two distinct oracle namespaces (O-022..O-030 from prior plan_engine and OR-FPS-006..OR-FPS-036 from prior plan_fps) are simultaneously load-bearing for the current acceptance suite. Reusing the same OR-FPS-* numbering or O-* numbering for new plan_vanilla_parity oracles would silently collide with these locked tests; future Phase 02 steps that introduce new oracles must allocate new identifiers above OR-FPS-036 (or define a new namespace) rather than reusing existing IDs. plan_engine/REFERENCE_ORACLES.md and plan_fps/REFERENCE_ORACLES.md are the authoritative registries for the two inherited namespaces and remain read-only under plan_vanilla_parity governance.",
    "The closed-enum set of fixture-load lock kinds (lock-via-bun-file-json-load, lock-via-bun-file-text-json-parse, lock-via-bun-file-text-load, lock-via-json-module-import, lock-via-node-readfilesync) records every load mechanism currently in use across the 41 tests. Future fixture-locking tests under plan_vanilla_parity should reuse one of these kinds rather than invent a new strategy, both to keep the load patterns under test/parity/ and test/oracles/ uniform and to avoid silently breaking the focused inventory test that asserts every observed lock kind belongs to this closed-enum set.",
    "The single test/parity/final-gate.test.ts is the only test in this inventory whose primary anchor is a manifest under reference/manifests/ (c1-complete.json) instead of a fixture under test/<group>/fixtures/. The c1-complete.json manifest is the side-by-side gate that records the O-030 full-shareware-e1-acceptance oracle as well as the priorOracleIds chain O-022..O-029, the bundled demo SHA-256 hashes, and the bundled DOS executable SHA-256 hashes. Any update to that manifest must coordinate with the same focused test, with full-e1-acceptance.test.ts (which embeds the same expected hashes), and with reference/manifests/file-hashes.json (which independently records the executable hashes).",
    "Some parity tests (test/parity/audio-suite.test.ts, test/parity/final-gate.test.ts, test/parity/framebuffer-crc.test.ts, test/parity/full-e1-acceptance.test.ts) also read the bundled local DOS executables (doom/DOOM.EXE, doom/DOOMD.EXE) at run time via reference/policy.ts REFERENCE_BUNDLE_PATH to verify shared anchor strings (\"High detail\", \"Low detail\", \"press a key.\", episode/map titles, etc.). These tests will fail if the bundled DOS binaries are not present at the configured REFERENCE_BUNDLE_PATH; the inventory does not embed those proprietary bytes and the boundary contract in reference/policy.ts and reference/manifests/file-hashes.json remains the authoritative gate for their availability and SHA-256 fingerprints.",
    "Because each test records its on-disk SHA-256 fingerprint in this inventory, any structural rewrite of a test (such as a global formatter sweep that changes Prettier output, an import-order migration, or a switch from Bun.file to readFileSync) will diverge from the captured snapshot and require a follow-up update to this inventory. The focused test enforces that divergence by recomputing each fingerprint at test time; a stale inventory will fail rather than silently mask a test rewrite that breaks the lock.",
    "test/parity/ and test/oracles/ are the only two top-level test directories under test/ that exclusively house fixture-locking tests in this codebase. Other test directories (test/playable/, test/vanilla_parity/, test/audio/, test/wad/, etc.) contain unit/integration tests that may load fixtures incidentally but do not carry primary oracle identifiers in this inventory. Any future migration that splits the parity oracle suite into a new directory (for example a plan_vanilla_parity/parity/ workspace) must update this inventory and the plan_vanilla_parity Phase 02 oracle-capture step files in lockstep."
  ],
